President Obama spoke with Prime Minister Sheikh Hasina of Bangladesh and Prime Minister Meles of Ethiopia to discuss climate change and the upcoming Leaders summit in Copenhagen. The President emphasized his commitment to making progress on climate change and encouraged both leaders to work towards a robust agreement. Prime Minister Hasina expressed appreciation for the efforts of the United States and highlighted the potential negative impact of climate change on Bangladesh's population. The two leaders agreed on the importance of working closely with the Danish Prime Minister and encouraging all countries to play a constructive role. With Prime Minister Meles, the President discussed the United States' efforts on climate change and praised the Prime Minister's leadership role in African countries. They also stressed the importance of success in Copenhagen and finding ways to make progress on mitigation, adaptation, and financing for developing countries.